# Boom Warehouse — E-Commerce & Inventory Platform

## Project Overview
Production e-commerce platform and inventory management system for Boom Warehouse,
a Cleveland-area refurbished electronics and appliance retailer with two physical
locations in Warrensville Heights and Cleveland, OH.

## Business Context
- Retail warehouse: refurbished electronics, appliances, TVs, computers, furniture
- Locations: 4554 Renaissance Pkwy (Warrensville Heights) + 26055 Emery Rd B-1 (Cleveland)
- Acima lease-to-own partnership (up to $5,000)
- Website: boomwarehouse.com (currently non-functional, this is the digital launch)

## Monorepo Structure
```
boom-warehouse/
├── .factory/
│   ├── agents.md
│   ├── droids/
│   ├── commands/
│   └── skills/boom-inventory/
├── apps/
│   ├── storefront/                # Next.js 15 — customer-facing store
│   ├── admin/                     # Next.js 15 — warehouse staff dashboard
│   └── api/                       # Fastify 5 — REST API
├── packages/
│   ├── db/                        # Drizzle schema + migrations
│   ├── shared/                    # Zod schemas, types, utilities
│   └── config/                    # Shared eslint, tsconfig
├── docker-compose.yml
├── Dockerfile, Dockerfile.admin, Dockerfile.api
└── .github/workflows/deploy.yml
```

## Technical Stack
- **Frontend**: Next.js 15, React 19, Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion
- **Admin**: Next.js 15, shadcn/ui, Recharts, quagga2 (barcode scanning)
- **API**: Fastify 5, TypeScript strict, Zod validation
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 16 via Drizzle ORM
- **Cache**: Redis 7
- **Search**: Meilisearch v1.7
- **Auth**: Auth.js v5 (JWT)
- **Payments**: Stripe + Acima lease-to-own
- **Storage**: Cloudflare R2 + CDN
- **Automation**: n8n (self-hosted on Hostinger VPS)
- **Hosting**: Hostinger Cloud Enterprise + VPS
- **CI/CD**: GitHub Actions → Docker Compose deploy

## Compound Engineering Integration

### Plugin Droids (from compound-engineering)
- `compound-engineering:review:security-sentinel` — Security audit
- `compound-engineering:review:performance-oracle` — Perf analysis
- `compound-engineering:review:kieran-typescript-reviewer` — TS best practices
- `compound-engineering:review:architecture-strategist` — Architecture compliance
- `compound-engineering:review:code-simplicity-reviewer` — YAGNI/simplicity
- `compound-engineering:review:data-integrity-guardian` — DB + data safety
- `compound-engineering:research:best-practices-researcher` — External research
- `compound-engineering:research:framework-docs-researcher` — Framework docs

### Custom Droids (project-specific)
- `boom-storefront` — E-commerce frontend (compounds frontend-design skill)
- `boom-inventory-api` — Inventory REST API (compounds boom-inventory skill)
- `boom-admin` — Admin dashboard
- `boom-infra` — Docker/Hostinger/CI-CD

### MCP Servers (already configured globally)
- **Serena** — Semantic code retrieval and editing (LSP-powered)
- **context7** — Up-to-date framework documentation lookup
- **Playwright** — Browser testing

## Quality Standards
- TypeScript strict mode, zero `any`
- 80%+ coverage (Vitest + Playwright + Supertest)
- Core Web Vitals: LCP < 2.5s, CLS < 0.1, INP < 200ms
- Mobile-first responsive
- OWASP security checklist
- Every component: error boundary + loading state + empty state

## Conventions
- Files: kebab-case. Components: PascalCase.
- API: /api/resource (REST, plural nouns)
- DB: snake_case
- Commits: conventional (feat:, fix:, chore:)
- Branches: feature/*, fix/*, chore/*

## Design Direction
- Palette: Navy (#1B3A5C) + Orange (#E8792B) + Charcoal (#2D2D2D)
- No generic AI aesthetics (no Inter, no purple gradients)
- Bold, warehouse-industrial aesthetic
- Product photography + clear pricing prominence
- Condition badges (New/Refurbished/Open Box) + stock indicators
- Lease-to-own CTA at product and checkout level
